From: Saurav Kashyap <saurav.kashyap@qlogic.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Aug 2011 11:31:50 -0700
Subject: qla2xxx: During loopdown perform Diagnostic loopback.
Git-commit: scsi-misc 491118dff9aeb207408bd42aa4897bc2c145747f
References: bnc#718279
Patch-Mainline: Included in scsi-misc

Signed-off-by: Saurav Kashyap <saurav.kashyap@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: Chad Dupuis <chad.dupuis@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: James Bottomley <JBottomley@Parallels.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_bsg.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_bsg.c b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_bsg.c
index 07d1767..e5954a4 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_bsg.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_bsg.c
@@ -704,6 +704,7 @@ qla2x00_process_loopback(struct fc_bsg_job *bsg_job)
 	elreq.options = bsg_job->request->rqst_data.h_vendor.vendor_cmd[1];
 
 	if ((ha->current_topology == ISP_CFG_F ||
+	    (atomic_read(&vha->loop_state) == LOOP_DOWN) ||
 	    (IS_QLA81XX(ha) &&
 	    le32_to_cpu(*(uint32_t *)req_data) == ELS_OPCODE_BYTE
 	    && req_data_len == MAX_ELS_FRAME_PAYLOAD)) &&
